{'contentformat': 'text/x-wiki', 'contentmodel': 'wikitext', '*': '{{PokémonPrevNext/Head|type=Normal}}\n{{PokémonPrevNext/GO|species=Slakoth}}\n{{PokémonPrevNext/Pokémon|type=Normal|prevnum=286|prev=Breloom|nextnum=288|next=Vigoroth|roundleft=bl|roundright=br}}\n|}\n{{Pokémon Infobox\n|name=Slakoth\n|jname=ナマケロ\n|tmname=Namakero\n|ndex=287\n|hdex=036\n|hdex6=037\n|u2dex=276\n|fbrow=162\n|abrow=032\n|typebox=1\n|type1=Normal\n|category=Slacker\n|height-ftin=2\'07"\n|height-m=0.8\n|weight-lbs=52.9\n|weight-kg=24.0\n|abilityn=1\n|abilitylayout=1\n|ability1=Truant\n|egggroupn=1\n|egggroup1=Field\n|eggcycles=15\n|evtotal=1\n|evhp=1\n|expyield=56\n|oldexp=83\n|lv100exp=1,250,000\n|gendercode=127\n|color=Brown\n|catchrate=255\n|body=08\n|pokefordex=slakoth\n|generation=3\n|friendship=70\n}}\n\'\'\'Slakoth\'\'\' ([[List of Japanese Pokémon names|Japanese]]: \'\'\'ナマケロ\'\'\' \'\'Namakero\'\') is a {{type|Normal}} {{OBP|Pokémon|species}} introduced in [[Generation III]].\n\nIt [[Evolution|evolves]] into {{p|Vigoroth}} starting at [[level]] 18, which evolves into {{p|Slaking}} starting at [[level]] 36.\n\n==Biology==\nSlakoth is a brown, quadruped Pokémon with sloth-like qualities. It has coarse, shaggy fur with two dark brown stripes on its back. There is a scruff of fur on top of its head, and it has a large, pig-like pink nose, pink eyelids, and dark rings around its eyes. It has long, lanky arms, but shorter legs. Each paw has two sharp claws, and there are pink paw pads on the back feet. Its underbelly and read are also pink.\n\nSlakoth lolls around and sleeps for more than twenty hours a day, which can make those around it drowsy. Since it does not move very much, it does not need much food and only eats three leaves each day. Its heart only beats once a minute. It is capable of regaining lost energy through use of its former [[signature move]], {{m|Slack Off}}. It makes its nest in {{DL|List of Pokémon by habitat|Forest Pokémon|tropical forests}}, and keeps the same one during its entire life. However, it can travel far by swimming in rivers.\n\n==In the anime==\n[[File:Marcel Slakoth.png|thumb|210px|left|Slakoth in the {{pkmn|anime}}]]\n===Major appearances===\nSlakoth physically debuted in \'\'[[AG069|Love, Petalburg Style]]\'\' and \'\'[[AG070|Balance of Power]]\'\', under the ownership of [[Norman]]. It was used in his [[Gym]] {{pkmn|battle}} against {{Ash}}, where it battled {{AP|Pikachu}} and {{AP|Torkoal}}. It proved to be a strong battler against Pikachu with its powerful {{m|Blizzard}} attack, but it lost to Torkoal\'s {{m|Flamethrower}}.\n\nMultiple Slakoth appeared in \'\'[[AG088|The Garden of Eatin\']]\'\'. They lived in the [[Banana Slakoth Garden]], which is run by [[Marcel]]. A {{p|Snorlax}} was eating all of the bananas in the garden and no one was able to stop it until one of the Slakoth in the garden evolved into {{p|Vigoroth}} and defeated it.\n\n===Minor appearances===\nSlakoth debuted in [[Max]]\'s flashback in \'\'[[AG034|Having a Wailord of a Time]]\'\'.\n\nA Slakoth appeared in \'\'[[AG119|The Ribbon Cup Caper]]\'\' at the [[S.S. St. Flower]]\'s [[Pokémon Center]].\n\nA Slakoth appeared in \'\'[[DP029|The Champ Twins!]]\'\'.\n\nA Slakoth appeared in \'\'[[DP088|Camping It Up!]]\'\', where {{OBP|Mitchell|DP088}} used it during the first activity of the [[Pokémon Summer Academy]].\n\nA Slakoth appeared in \'\'[[DP090|Ghoul Daze!]]\'\'.\n\nA {{pkmn|Coordinator}}\'s Slakoth appeared in \'\'[[DP162|Playing the Performance Encore!]]\'\', where it was used in the [[Contest Battle|Battle Stage]] of the {{to|Daybreak}} {{pkmn|Contest}} along with a {{p|Shroomish}}.\n\nA Slakoth appeared in \'\'[[XY002|Lumiose City Pursuit!]]\'\'.\n\n===Pokédex entries===\n{{Animedexheader|Hoenn}}\n{{Animedexbody|AG069|Slakoth|May\'s Pokédex|Slakoth, the Slacker Pokémon. Slakoth is generally found sleeping and very few ever witness it in motion.}}\n{{Animedexfooter/Pokémon|\'\'Advanced Generation\'\'|Hoenn}}\n\n==In the manga==\n[[File:Slokath Amnesia.png|thumb|200px|Slakoth in [[Pokémon Adventures]]]]\n===In the Ash & Pikachu manga===\n[[Norman]]\'s Slakoth appeared in \'\'[[SP25|I\'ll Win With My Own Battle Style!!]]\'\'.\n\n===In the Pokémon Adventures manga===\nA Slakoth, nicknamed Slokath (Japanese: \'\'\'ケンタロ\'\'\' \'\'Kentarō\'\'), under the ownership of Alecsey (Japanese: \'\'\'ヒロキ\'\'\' \'\'Hiroki\'\'), appeared in a Pokémon Contest in \'\'[[PS200|Tripped Up by Torkoal]]\'\'.\n\nIn \'\'[[PS264|It All Ends Now V]]\'\', [[Norman]] was seen with two Slakoth that he used to try to stop {{DL|Super-ancient Pokémon (Adventures)|Rayquaza}} from fleeing from its confines.\n\nA Slakoth appeared in \'\'[[PS525|The Transfer Student]]\'\'.\n\n===In the Pokémon Ruby-Sapphire manga===\nIn the [[Pokémon Ruby-Sapphire]] manga, Norman owns a Slakoth. In \'\'[[PMRS04|There\'s Someone More Important Than Clefairy?!]]\'\', it swallows the {{badge|Balance}} and [[Red\'s Clefairy]] helps to retrieve it from its stomach.\n\n==In the TCG==\n{{main|Slakoth (TCG)}}\n\n==Game data==\n===NPC appearances===\n* {{ga|Pokémon Ranger}}: [[Go-Rock Quads|Clyde]] uses a Slakoth to back up his {{p|Slaking}}.\n* [[Pokémon Mystery Dungeon: Explorers of Time and Explorers of Darkness]]: Slakoth and {{p|Slowpoke}} are the members of Team Slacker, the zero-motivation exploration team.\n\n===Pokédex entries===\n{{Dex/Header|type=Normal}}\n{{Dex/NA|gen=III}}\n{{Dex/Gen/2|gen=III|reg1=Hoenn|num1=036|reg2=Kanto}}\n{{Dex/Entry1|v=Ruby|t=FFF|entry=Slakoth lolls around for over twenty hours every day. Because it moves so little, it does not need much food. This Pokémon\'s sole daily meal consists of just three leaves.}}\n{{Dex/Entry1|v=Sapphire|t=FFF|entry=Slakoth\'s heart beats just once a minute. Whatever happens, it is content to loaf around motionless. It is rare to see this Pokémon in motion.}}\n{{Dex/Entry1|v=Emerald|t=FFF|entry=It sleeps virtually all day and night long. It doesn\'t change its nest its entire life, but it some